<subSubSection id="AE6A6471688A8CD561755035349EF600" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph id="02E3504B8E2B6F9D80522A0A1CFBE95A" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0955425F1501BACED545DDF99F1698AA" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
No other original material was found in the surveyed herbaria. According to the label, this plant was originally collected in Reculet and then grown in 
<normalizedToken id="25A4B331509BC7DA55F8A28C391D6085" originalValue="Jordan’s">Jordan's</normalizedToken>
garden, where it was collected in July. As a matter of fact, besides his huge herbarium and library, Alexis Jordan owned a one-hectare experimental garden. We know that he used it to sow most species every year, while maintaining alive perennial ones, and that he regularly made herbarium sheets from these cultivated plants. In this context, the notion of original material requires particular attention (
<bibRefCitation id="E1C7637071013597871E700E321EFCBF" DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/phytotaxa.269.2.3" author="Thiebaut, M" journalOrPublisher="Phytotaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="103 - 112" refId="B35" refString="Thiebaut, M, Tison, J-M, 2016. Typification of thirty-two names given by Alexis Jordan in the genus Biscutella (Brassicaceae). Phytotaxa 269 (2): 103 - 112, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/phytotaxa.269.2.3" title="Typification of thirty-two names given by Alexis Jordan in the genus Biscutella (Brassicaceae)." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/phytotaxa.269.2.3" volume="269" year="2016">Thiebaut and Tison 2016</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2B148FE79C2914253A82FE857097E783" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
The lectotype designated here matches the protologue and corresponds to the current application of the name, which is considered a heterotypic synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="2CBA4D60271AA0D7FECBF56438724FD4" family="Caryophyllaceae" genus="D." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="D. godronianus" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="godronianus">
<emphasis id="FA9AF855F9E79DACF06922F44A7438C0" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">D. godronianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Jord. in 
<bibRefCitation id="C47B47C2D03F5D1757C41558F9425A81" author="Kerguelen, M" journalOrPublisher="Naturalia, Turriers" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B26" refString="Kerguelen, M, 1993. Index synonymique de la flore de France. Museum national d'histoire naturelle, Paris." title="Index synonymique de la flore de France. Museum national d'histoire naturelle, Paris." year="1993">
<normalizedToken id="DF644E8B092E3D0D8C669FA39779FF1D" originalValue="Kerguélen">Kerguelen</normalizedToken>
(1993)
</bibRefCitation>
, in turn, currently considered a heterotypic synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="996E17C7E54DB89A535879024F33B59A" family="Caryophyllaceae" genus="D." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="D. virgineus" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="virgineus">
<emphasis id="DA68A6A27E4EC9D81F4DD909B339B955" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">D. virgineus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="D242A07F4D13CC58F2FB1AFE172D557C" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1002/tax.12563" author="Domina, G" journalOrPublisher="Taxon" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="1096 - 1100" refId="B15" refString="Domina, G, Astuti, G, Barone, G, Gargano, D, Minuto, L, Varaldo, L, Peruzzi, L, 2021. Lectotypification of the name Dianthus virgineus and consequences within the D. sylvestris group (Caryophyllaceae). Taxon 70 (5): 1096 - 1100, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1002/tax.12563" title="Lectotypification of the name Dianthus virgineus and consequences within the D. sylvestris group (Caryophyllaceae)." url="https://doi.org/10.1002/tax.12563" volume="70" year="2021">Domina et al. 2021</bibRefCitation>
). The lectotype of 
<taxonomicName id="683BA5C1341274EF99327EF194DE138B" family="Caryophyllaceae" genus="D." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="D. aggericola" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="aggericola">
<emphasis id="D06F8EE484DC07C8BAE4D59409AF30EE" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">D. aggericola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and that of 
<taxonomicName id="CBC4072E0BD90A09F2A53E47D42F77C1" family="Caryophyllaceae" genus="D." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="D. virgineus" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="virgineus">
<emphasis id="04732A2EBDEB553B376735B6FA9FFF51" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">D. virgineus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, have the same leaf length and width, uniflowered scapes, the same length and shape of outer and inner bracts, the same calyx length and shape. We, therefore, confirm this synonymy.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
